race.comment: ICON DREAM (8) struck trouble early and never got into the contest when fifth over 2100m at Orange. Expected to bounce back after his solid second two-back at Kembla. Hard to beat in this suitable race. MY GREEK GOD (3) produced a reasonable effort when third last start after being in the firing line on the turn over 2000m at Kembla Grange. That followed a win at Newcastle the start prior. Well placed and can take stopping from the good barrier. LILY DARLING (6) ran fifth at her latest appearance over 2200m at this track and will relish Small's claim again. Best form is good enough to take this out. SAINTLY SANDS (7) is close to a win after a sequence of minor placings and gives the indication she will appreciate the extra trip. Surged late from back in the pack when third over 1600m at this track. Don't underestimate.
